<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Premier-League-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&#038;ssl=1" alt="Russia blocks Premier League broadcasts by Amazon&#8217;s Twitch over lawsuit" align="left" style="margin: 0 20px 20px 0;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1" /> A Russian court has blocked access to English Premier League game broadcasts by Amazon’s Twitch after Russia’s Rambler media group said it would sue the video streaming service over pirate broadcasts, the TASS news agency reported. Rambler plans to sue Twitch for 180 billion roubles ($2.82 billion) in a Russian court for what it said were 36,000 cases in which Twitch had violated its rights to broadcast the soccer games, the Kommersant newspaper reported earlier on Monday. Continue reading Russia blocks Premier League broadcasts by Amazon’s Twitch over lawsuit at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard